{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":28755,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":true}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🧠 Gemma 3 AI News Summarizer — Kaggle Training Notebook\n\n**Model**: `google/gemma-3-4b-it` or `google/gemma-3-12b-it` (text-only, via `kagglehub`)\n**Method**: QLoRA (4-bit NF4 quantisation + LoRA adapters)\n**Library**: TRL `SFTTrainer` + PEFT\n**Hardware**: Kaggle T4 × 2 (16 GB VRAM each = 32 GB total)\n**Est. Time**: ~45 min (4B) · ~90 min (12B) for 1 epoch on 3 500 examples\n\n---\n\n## Why Gemma 3 instead of Gemma 4?\n\n| | Gemma 4 E4B | Gemma 3 4B | Gemma 3 12B |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Architecture | Multimodal | Text-only ✅ | Text-only ✅ |\n| T4 VRAM (4-bit) | ~9 GB | ~5 GB ✅ | ~9 GB ✅ |\n| `AutoTokenizer` | ❌ (needs Processor) | ✅ | ✅ |\n| BF16 support | Required (T4 ❌) | FP16 fine ✅ | FP16 fine ✅ |\n| Fine-tune stability | ⚠️ Fragile | ✅ Excellent | ✅ Excellent |\n\nGemma 4 is a multimodal model. Its vision tower adds memory overhead and\nthe `AutoProcessor` path is fragile on T4 GPUs. For **text summarization**,\nGemma 3 is faster, lighter, and fully supported by TRL out of the box.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Prerequisites (do these BEFORE running)\n\n1. Go to https://www.kaggle.com/models/google/gemma-3\n2. Click **\"Request Access\"** → **\"Verify via Kaggle Account\"** → Submit\n3. Attach the model: Add-ons → Models → search **\"gemma-3\"** → add `gemma-3-4b-it`\n4. Enable GPU: Settings → Accelerator → **GPU T4 × 2**\n5. Attach your dataset: Add-ons → Datasets → **`deetyam/gemma-news-data`**\n\n## ♻️ Checkpoint / Resume\n\n- Checkpoints are saved every 10 optimiser steps to `/kaggle/working/checkpoints/`.\n- To resume, set `RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT = True` in Section 4 — the latest checkpoint\n  is found automatically.\n- To resume from a specific checkpoint, set it to the path string (e.g. `\"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/checkpoint-80\"`).","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Install Dependencies\n\n> Run this cell first, then **restart the kernel** before continuing.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ─── Install / upgrade required packages ────────────────────────────────────\n# Run once, then restart the kernel.\n!pip install -q \\\n    \"transformers>=4.46.0\" \\\n    \"peft>=0.13.0\" \\\n    \"trl>=0.12.0\" \\\n    \"bitsandbytes>=0.43.0\" \\\n    \"accelerate>=0.34.0\" \\\n    \"datasets\" \\\n    \"rouge_score\"\n\n# Ensure we have the latest compatible versions\n!pip install -q --upgrade transformers peft trl\n\nprint(\"\\n✅ Installation complete — restart the kernel now, then continue from Section 2.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Imports & GPU Check","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import gc\nimport glob\nimport json\nimport os\nimport re\nimport shutil\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport kagglehub  # pre-installed on Kaggle\nimport torch\nfrom datasets import Dataset, DatasetDict\nfrom peft import (\n    LoraConfig,\n    get_peft_model,\n    prepare_model_for_kbit_training,\n)\nfrom transformers import (\n    AutoModelForCausalLM,\n    AutoTokenizer,           # ← Gemma 3 is text-only: plain AutoTokenizer\n    BitsAndBytesConfig,\n)\nfrom trl import SFTConfig, SFTTrainer\n\n# ── Sanity-check the runtime ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(f\"PyTorch  : {torch.__version__}\")\nprint(f\"CUDA     : {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n\nif not torch.cuda.is_available():\n    raise RuntimeError(\n        \"No GPU detected! Enable GPU: Settings → Accelerator → GPU T4 × 2\"\n    )\n\nfor i in range(torch.cuda.device_count()):\n    props = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(i)\n    vram  = props.total_memory / 1e9\n    print(f\"  GPU {i} : {props.name}  ({vram:.1f} GB)\")\n\n    # Warn if BF16 is not supported (T4 doesn't support it)\n    if not props.is_bf16_supported if hasattr(props, 'is_bf16_supported') else True:\n        print(f\"         ⚠️  BF16 not supported — will use FP16\")\n\nprint(\"\\n✅ Environment OK\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Download Gemma 3 via kagglehub\n\nGemma 3 is a **text-only** model — no vision tower, no processor complexity.\nUse Kaggle's native model hosting: no HuggingFace token needed.\n\n### Available variants\n\n| Variant | Kaggle handle | VRAM (4-bit) | Est. training time |\n|---------|---------------|-------------|--------------------|\n| **4B-IT** ← default | `google/gemma-3/transformers/gemma-3-4b-it` | ~5 GB | ~45 min |\n| 12B-IT | `google/gemma-3/transformers/gemma-3-12b-it` | ~9 GB | ~90 min |\n| 27B-IT | `google/gemma-3/transformers/gemma-3-27b-it` | ~18 GB | ⚠️ Needs 2× A100 |\n\nFor T4 × 2 (32 GB total), both 4B and 12B work comfortably.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ─── Choose your Gemma 3 variant ────────────────────────────────────────────\n# 4B  → faster, ~45 min, good quality\n# 12B → slower, ~90 min, better quality (recommended if time allows)\nKAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE = \"google/gemma-3/transformers/gemma-3-4b-it\"\n# KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE = \"google/gemma-3/transformers/gemma-3-12b-it\"  # uncomment for 12B\n\nprint(f\"⬇  Downloading model: {KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE}\")\nMODEL_PATH = kagglehub.model_download(KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE)\nprint(f\"✅ Model path : {MODEL_PATH}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Configuration\n\n### ♻️ Checkpoint / Resume Settings\n\n| `RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT` | Behaviour |\n|---|---|\n| `False` | Start a brand-new training run |\n| `True` | Auto-detect and resume from the **latest** checkpoint in `OUTPUT_DIR` |\n| `\"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/checkpoint-80\"` | Resume from that **specific** checkpoint |","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"OUTPUT_DIR  = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints\"\nADAPTER_DIR = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/final_adapter\"\n\n# ── Checkpoint / Resume ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# True  → resume from latest checkpoint automatically\n# False → start fresh\n# str   → resume from that specific checkpoint directory\nRESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT = True\n\n# ── Training hyperparameters ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Tuned for Gemma 3 4B on T4 × 2 with QLoRA\n# For 12B: lower BATCH_SIZE to 1\nLORA_R        = 16\nLORA_ALPHA    = 32\nLORA_DROPOUT  = 0.05\nMAX_SEQ_LEN   = 512\nBATCH_SIZE    = 2     # use 1 for 12B\nGRAD_ACCUM    = 8     # effective batch = 16\nLR            = 2e-4\nEPOCHS        = 1\nWARMUP_STEPS  = 10\nSAVE_STEPS    = 10    # save every 10 steps — frequent enough to survive Kaggle kills\n\n# ── Prompt templates (Gemma 3 text summarization) ─────────────────────────────\nSTYLE_TEMPLATES = {\n    \"short\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news summarizer. \"\n        \"Write a concise 2–3 sentence summary of the following article. \"\n        \"Preserve key entities, dates, and findings.\\n\\nArticle:\\n{article}\\n\\nSummary:\"\n    ),\n    \"bullet\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news summarizer. \"\n        \"Extract the 4–6 most important points from the article as concise bullet points.\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nKey Points:\"\n    ),\n    \"headline\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news editor. \"\n        \"First write a punchy headline, then write a 2-sentence summary.\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nHeadline and Summary:\"\n    ),\n    \"detailed\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news analyst. \"\n        \"Provide a detailed structured summary with: \"\n        \"1) Headline 2) Main Summary (3–4 sentences) \"\n        \"3) Key Points (bullet list) 4) Takeaway (one sentence).\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nStructured Summary:\"\n    ),\n}\n\n# Gemma 3 uses the same <start_of_turn> / <end_of_turn> chat template as Gemma 2\nCHAT_TEMPLATE = (\n    \"<start_of_turn>user\\n{prompt}<end_of_turn>\\n\"\n    \"<start_of_turn>model\\n{response}<end_of_turn>\"\n)\n\nprint(\"✅ Configuration set\")\nprint(f\"   Model variant    : {KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE.split('/')[-1]}\")\nprint(f\"   LoRA rank        : {LORA_R}\")\nprint(f\"   Effective batch  : {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\nprint(f\"   Learning rate    : {LR}\")\nprint(f\"   Max seq length   : {MAX_SEQ_LEN}\")\nprint(f\"   Save every steps : {SAVE_STEPS}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4b. Checkpoint Detection\n\nThis cell resolves the `RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT` setting to a concrete path\n(or `None` for a fresh start) and lists all available checkpoints.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def _find_latest_checkpoint(output_dir: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Return the checkpoint directory with the highest step number, or None.\"\"\"\n    pattern    = os.path.join(output_dir, \"checkpoint-*\")\n    candidates = [c for c in glob.glob(pattern) if os.path.isdir(c)]\n    if not candidates:\n        return None\n\n    def _step(path):\n        m = re.search(r\"checkpoint-(\\d+)$\", path)\n        return int(m.group(1)) if m else -1\n\n    return max(candidates, key=_step)\n\n\n# ── Resolve to a concrete path ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nif isinstance(RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT, str):\n    _resume_path = RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT\n    if not os.path.isdir(_resume_path):\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"Checkpoint directory not found: {_resume_path!r}\\n\"\n            \"Check the path or set RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT = False.\"\n        )\nelif RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT is True:\n    _resume_path = _find_latest_checkpoint(OUTPUT_DIR)\nelse:\n    _resume_path = None\n\n# ── Report ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nif _resume_path:\n    all_ckpts = sorted(\n        glob.glob(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"checkpoint-*\")),\n        key=lambda p: int(re.search(r\"checkpoint-(\\d+)$\", p).group(1))\n        if re.search(r\"checkpoint-(\\d+)$\", p) else -1,\n    )\n    print(\"📂 Available checkpoints:\")\n    for ckpt in all_ckpts:\n        marker = \"  ← RESUMING\" if ckpt == _resume_path else \"\"\n        print(f\"   {ckpt}{marker}\")\n    print(f\"\\n♻️  Will resume from: {_resume_path}\")\nelse:\n    print(\"🆕 No checkpoint found — starting a fresh training run.\")\n    print(f\"   Checkpoints will be saved to: {OUTPUT_DIR}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. Load Tokenizer\n\nGemma 3 is **text-only**, so we use the standard `AutoTokenizer` —\nno `AutoProcessor`, no multimodal overhead.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Loading tokenizer from local model path …\")\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_PATH)\n\n# Gemma 3 has a dedicated <pad> token — no need to reuse <eos>\nif tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n\n# padding_side=\"right\" is required for correct SFT loss masking\ntokenizer.padding_side = \"right\"\n\nprint(f\"✅ Vocab size    : {tokenizer.vocab_size:,}\")\nprint(f\"   Pad token    : {tokenizer.pad_token!r}\")\nprint(f\"   EOS token    : {tokenizer.eos_token!r}\")\nprint(f\"   BOS token    : {tokenizer.bos_token!r}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Load Dataset\n\n**Option A** — Attach your Kaggle Dataset `deetyam/gemma-news-data`\n(Add-ons → Datasets), which provides `train.jsonl` and `val.jsonl`.\n\n**Option B** — Place `sample_dataset.jsonl` directly under `/kaggle/input/`.\n\nEach JSONL record must have keys:\n- `article` (str) — the news article text\n- `summary` (str) — the target summary\n- `style` (str) — one of `short`, `bullet`, `headline`, `detailed`\n- `headline` (str, optional)\n- `key_points` (list[str], optional)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def load_jsonl(path: str) -> list[dict]:\n    records = []\n    with open(path, encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        for line in f:\n            line = line.strip()\n            if line:\n                records.append(json.loads(line))\n    return records\n\n\ndef build_target(record: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build the model's target output from a dataset record.\"\"\"\n    style      = record.get(\"style\", \"detailed\")\n    summary    = record.get(\"summary\", \"\")\n    headline   = record.get(\"headline\", \"\")\n    key_points = record.get(\"key_points\", [])\n\n    if style == \"short\":\n        return summary\n    if style == \"bullet\":\n        pts = key_points or [s.strip() for s in summary.split(\".\") if s.strip()]\n        return \"\\n\".join(f\"• {p}\" for p in pts[:5])\n    if style == \"headline\":\n        return f\"**{headline}**\\n\\n{summary}\" if headline else summary\n\n    # detailed\n    parts = []\n    if headline:   parts.append(f\"**Headline:** {headline}\")\n    if summary:    parts.append(f\"\\n**Summary:** {summary}\")\n    if key_points:\n        pts = \"\\n\".join(f\"• {p}\" for p in key_points)\n        parts.append(f\"\\n**Key Points:**\\n{pts}\")\n    takeaway = key_points[-1] if key_points else \"\"\n    if takeaway:   parts.append(f\"\\n**Takeaway:** {takeaway}\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(parts)\n\n\ndef format_record(record: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Format a dataset record into a single text string for SFT.\"\"\"\n    style  = record.get(\"style\", \"detailed\")\n    prompt = STYLE_TEMPLATES[style].format(article=record[\"article\"].strip())\n    target = build_target(record)\n    text   = CHAT_TEMPLATE.format(prompt=prompt, response=target)\n    return {\"text\": text}\n\n\n# ── Resolve dataset paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTRAIN_FILE = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/deetyam/gemma-news-data/train.jsonl\"\nVAL_FILE   = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/deetyam/gemma-news-data/val.jsonl\"\n\nif not Path(TRAIN_FILE).exists():\n    print(\"⚠ Processed splits not found — falling back to sample_dataset.jsonl\")\n    TRAIN_FILE = \"/kaggle/input/gemma-news-summarizer/data/sample_dataset.jsonl\"\n    VAL_FILE   = None\n\ntrain_records = load_jsonl(TRAIN_FILE)\nval_records   = load_jsonl(VAL_FILE) if VAL_FILE and Path(VAL_FILE).exists() else train_records[:10]\n\ntrain_data = [format_record(r) for r in train_records]\nval_data   = [format_record(r) for r in val_records]\n\nds = DatasetDict({\n    \"train\":      Dataset.from_list(train_data),\n    \"validation\": Dataset.from_list(val_data),\n})\n\nprint(f\"\\n✅ Dataset loaded:\")\nprint(f\"   Train : {len(ds['train'])} examples\")\nprint(f\"   Val   : {len(ds['validation'])} examples\")\nprint(f\"\\nSample text (first 400 chars):\")\nprint(ds[\"train\"][0][\"text\"][:400])","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 7. Load Base Model in 4-bit (QLoRA)\n\n### Key fixes vs. the previous Gemma 4 notebook\n\n| Issue | Old (broken) | New (fixed) |\n|---|---|---|\n| dtype | `torch_dtype=torch.float16` (deprecated) | `dtype=torch.float16` ✅ |\n| device_map | `{\"\":0}` (pins to GPU 0 only!) | `\"auto\"` (uses both T4s) ✅ |\n| Model architecture | Multimodal (vision tower) | Text-only ✅ |\n\n> **Why FP16, not BF16?**  \n> T4 GPUs do **not** support bfloat16 natively. Using `bf16=True` causes\n> silent hangs mid-training. FP16 is fully supported and equally stable for QLoRA.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 4-bit NF4 quantisation config ────────────────────────────────────────────\n# double_quant saves an extra ~0.4 GB with negligible quality loss\nbnb_config = BitsAndBytesConfig(\n    load_in_4bit=True,\n    bnb_4bit_quant_type=\"nf4\",\n    bnb_4bit_compute_dtype=torch.float16,   # FP16: supported on T4 ✅\n    bnb_4bit_use_double_quant=True,\n)\n\nprint(f\"Loading model from: {MODEL_PATH}\")\nprint(\"(4-bit NF4 + double quantisation, device_map='auto' across both GPUs)\")\n\n# ── Load model ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# FIX 1: use `dtype` (not deprecated `torch_dtype`)\n# FIX 2: device_map=\"auto\" lets accelerate split layers across both T4 GPUs\nmodel = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    MODEL_PATH,\n    quantization_config=bnb_config,\n    device_map=\"auto\",              # ✅ uses BOTH T4 GPUs\n    dtype=torch.float16,            # ✅ FP16 (BF16 is not supported on T4)\n    attn_implementation=\"eager\",    # safer than flash-attn on older GPUs\n)\n\nprint(f\"\\n✅ Model loaded\")\nprint(f\"   Memory footprint : {model.get_memory_footprint() / 1e9:.2f} GB\")\n\n# ── FIX 3: prepare_model_for_kbit_training ────────────────────────────────────\n# This is critical for stable QLoRA:\n#   - Casts LayerNorm weights to float32 (prevents NaN gradients)\n#   - Handles gradient checkpointing safely with quantised layers\n#   - Was incorrectly removed in the Gemma 4 notebook\ngc.collect()\ntorch.cuda.empty_cache()\n\nmodel = prepare_model_for_kbit_training(\n    model,\n    use_gradient_checkpointing=True,\n    gradient_checkpointing_kwargs={\"use_reentrant\": False},  # safer for multi-GPU\n)\n\nprint(\"   Gradient checkpointing   : enabled\")\nprint(\"   prepare_model_for_kbit   : done ✅\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 8. Apply LoRA Adapters\n\nGemma 3 (text-only) has a flat module hierarchy — no `language_model.*` prefix.\nWe target all attention projection layers and the MLP gating layers for best coverage.\n\n> **♻️ Resuming note:** When resuming, the LoRA adapter weights are\n> automatically loaded from the checkpoint by `SFTTrainer`. Just run\n> this cell as usual and proceed to training.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"lora_config = LoraConfig(\n    r=LORA_R,\n    lora_alpha=LORA_ALPHA,\n    # Gemma 3 text-only module names (no \"language_model\" prefix unlike Gemma 4)\n    target_modules=[\n        \"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\",   # attention\n        \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\",        # MLP\n    ],\n    lora_dropout=LORA_DROPOUT,\n    bias=\"none\",\n    task_type=\"CAUSAL_LM\",\n)\n\nmodel = get_peft_model(model, lora_config)\nmodel.print_trainable_parameters()\n# Expected: ~0.4–0.8% of total params for r=16 on 4B model\n# Example:  trainable params: 27,262,976 || all params: 4,299,694,080 || trainable%: 0.634","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 9. Train\n\n### Key fixes vs. the previous Gemma 4 notebook\n\n| Setting | Old (broken) | New (fixed) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `bf16` | `True` (T4 ❌) | `False` ✅ |\n| `fp16` | `False` | `True` ✅ |\n| `load_best_model_at_end` | `True` (hangs on quantised models) | `False` ✅ |\n| `save_steps` | `15` | `10` (more frequent, survives Kaggle kills) ✅ |\n\n### Checkpoint schedule\n\n| Setting | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `save_strategy` | `\"steps\"` | Save after every N steps |\n| `save_steps` | `10` | Checkpoint every 10 optimiser steps |\n| `save_total_limit` | `5` | Keep the 5 most recent checkpoints |\n| `load_best_model_at_end` | `False` | Skip the end-of-training reload (avoids hang) |","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"training_args = SFTConfig(\n    output_dir=OUTPUT_DIR,\n    num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,\n    per_device_train_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n    per_device_eval_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n    gradient_accumulation_steps=GRAD_ACCUM,\n    learning_rate=LR,\n    weight_decay=0.01,\n    warmup_steps=WARMUP_STEPS,\n    lr_scheduler_type=\"cosine\",\n    max_grad_norm=0.3,\n    logging_steps=5,\n    # ── dtype: FP16 ✅ (T4 does NOT support BF16!) ──────────────────────────\n    bf16=False,   # ← was True in Gemma 4 notebook — T4 does NOT support BF16!\n    fp16=True,    # ← correct for T4 GPUs\n    # ── Gradient checkpointing ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n    gradient_checkpointing=True,\n    gradient_checkpointing_kwargs={\"use_reentrant\": False},\n    # ── Checkpoint settings ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    save_strategy=\"steps\",\n    save_steps=SAVE_STEPS,       # every 10 steps — frequent enough to survive kills\n    save_total_limit=5,          # keep the 5 most recent checkpoints\n    load_best_model_at_end=False,  # ← True causes a reload hang with quantised models!\n    eval_strategy=\"steps\",\n    eval_steps=SAVE_STEPS,       # evaluate at the same cadence as saving\n    # ── SFT-specific ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    max_length=MAX_SEQ_LEN,\n    dataset_text_field=\"text\",\n    packing=False,\n    # ── Optimizer ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    optim=\"paged_adamw_8bit\",   # memory-efficient optimizer for QLoRA\n    # ── Logging ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    report_to=\"none\",           # set \"wandb\" if you have W&B configured\n)\n\ntrainer = SFTTrainer(\n    model=model,\n    train_dataset=ds[\"train\"],\n    eval_dataset=ds[\"validation\"],\n    args=training_args,\n    processing_class=tokenizer,\n)\n\n# ── Training summary ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nsteps_per_epoch = len(ds[\"train\"]) // (BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM)\ntotal_steps     = steps_per_epoch * EPOCHS\n\nprint(\"🚀 Starting training …\")\nprint(f\"   Model           : {KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE.split('/')[-1]}\")\nprint(f\"   Epochs          : {EPOCHS}\")\nprint(f\"   Steps per epoch : {steps_per_epoch}\")\nprint(f\"   Total steps     : {total_steps}\")\nprint(f\"   Effective batch : {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\nprint(f\"   Learning rate   : {LR}\")\nprint(f\"   Max seq length  : {MAX_SEQ_LEN}\")\nprint(f\"   Save every      : {SAVE_STEPS} steps\")\nif _resume_path:\n    print(f\"   ♻️  Resuming from : {_resume_path}\")\nelse:\n    print(\"   🆕 Starting fresh\")\nprint()\n\ntrainer.train(resume_from_checkpoint=_resume_path)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 10. Save LoRA Adapter","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Path(ADAPTER_DIR).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n# Save LoRA adapter weights\ntrainer.model.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_DIR)\n\n# Save tokenizer alongside the adapter\ntokenizer.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_DIR)\n\nprint(f\"✅ Adapter saved to: {ADAPTER_DIR}\")\nprint(f\"   Contents: {[p.name for p in Path(ADAPTER_DIR).iterdir()]}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 11. Quick Inference Test\n\nVerify the fine-tuned adapter actually works before downloading it.\nWe merge the LoRA weights into the base model for faster inference.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from peft import PeftModel\n\n# ── Reload base model and merge adapter ──────────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"Reloading base model for inference test …\")\nbase_infer = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    MODEL_PATH,\n    dtype=torch.float16,\n    device_map=\"auto\",\n)\nmodel_merged = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base_infer, ADAPTER_DIR)\nmodel_merged = model_merged.merge_and_unload()\nmodel_merged.eval()\nprint(\"✅ Merged model ready\")\n\n# ── Run a test summary ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTEST_ARTICLE = \"\"\"\nGoogle DeepMind released Gemini Ultra 2, claiming it surpasses GPT-5 on every major benchmark\nincluding MMLU, HumanEval, and MATH. The new model features a 4 million token context window\nand native multimodal processing across text, image, audio, and video. It will be available\nthrough Gemini Advanced subscriptions starting next month at no extra cost for current users.\n\"\"\"\n\nprompt    = STYLE_TEMPLATES[\"detailed\"].format(article=TEST_ARTICLE.strip())\nchat_msgs = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n\n# Gemma 3 supports apply_chat_template natively\nformatted = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n    chat_msgs, tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True\n)\n\ninputs     = tokenizer(formatted, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model_merged.device)\nprompt_len = inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n\nwith torch.inference_mode():\n    output_ids = model_merged.generate(\n        **inputs,\n        max_new_tokens=400,\n        temperature=0.7,\n        do_sample=True,\n        repetition_penalty=1.1,\n        pad_token_id=tokenizer.pad_token_id,\n        eos_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n    )\n\ngenerated = tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0][prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=True)\nprint(\"─\" * 60)\nprint(\"GENERATED SUMMARY:\")\nprint(\"─\" * 60)\nprint(generated)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 12. Zip & Download the Adapter\n\nAfter running this cell, go to the **Output** panel (right side of Kaggle) and\ndownload `final_adapter.zip`.\n\nExtract it on your local machine:\n```bash\nunzip final_adapter.zip -d checkpoints/final_adapter/\n```","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"zip_path = \"/kaggle/working/final_adapter\"\nshutil.make_archive(zip_path, \"zip\", ADAPTER_DIR)\n\nzip_size = Path(f\"{zip_path}.zip\").stat().st_size / 1e6\nprint(f\"✅ Zipped: {zip_path}.zip  ({zip_size:.0f} MB)\")\nprint()\nprint(\"Next steps:\")\nprint(\"  1. Download final_adapter.zip from the Kaggle Output panel (right side)\")\nprint(\"  2. Extract it on your machine:\")\nprint(\"       unzip final_adapter.zip -d checkpoints/final_adapter/\")\nprint(\"  3. Start the API server:\")\nprint(\"       uvicorn api.main:app --reload\")\nprint(\"  4. Open the frontend:\")\nprint(\"       cd frontend && npm run dev\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 13. (Optional) Evaluation with ROUGE Scores\n\nRun this cell after training to get quantitative ROUGE-1/2/L scores\non the validation set, so you can compare different training runs.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from rouge_score import rouge_scorer\n\nscorer = rouge_scorer.RougeScorer([\"rouge1\", \"rouge2\", \"rougeL\"], use_stemmer=True)\n\nresults = {\"rouge1\": [], \"rouge2\": [], \"rougeL\": []}\n\nprint(\"Evaluating on validation set …\")\nfor example in ds[\"validation\"].select(range(min(50, len(ds[\"validation\"])))):\n    # Extract the reference summary from the text field\n    text = example[\"text\"]\n    # The model output comes after <start_of_turn>model\\n\n    parts = text.split(\"<start_of_turn>model\\n\")\n    if len(parts) < 2:\n        continue\n    reference = parts[1].replace(\"<end_of_turn>\", \"\").strip()\n\n    # Generate a prediction\n    prompt_text = parts[0] + \"<start_of_turn>model\\n\"\n    inputs = tokenizer(\n        prompt_text,\n        return_tensors=\"pt\",\n        truncation=True,\n        max_length=MAX_SEQ_LEN,\n    ).to(model_merged.device)\n\n    prompt_len = inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n    with torch.inference_mode():\n        out = model_merged.generate(\n            **inputs,\n            max_new_tokens=200,\n            temperature=0.7,\n            do_sample=True,\n            pad_token_id=tokenizer.pad_token_id,\n            eos_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n        )\n    prediction = tokenizer.decode(out[0][prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=True)\n\n    scores = scorer.score(reference, prediction)\n    for k in results:\n        results[k].append(scores[k].fmeasure)\n\nprint(\"\\n📊 ROUGE Scores (mean over validation sample):\")\nfor k, vals in results.items():\n    mean_val = sum(vals) / len(vals) if vals else 0.0\n    print(f\"   {k.upper():8s}: {mean_val:.4f}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}